<tal:root
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  omit-tag="">
<tal:do-this-first condition="view/form_action" />
<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
  <body>
    <metal:heading fill-slot="pageheading">
      <h1>OpenPGP keys</h1> 
    </metal:heading>

  <metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  </metal:leftportlets>

  <div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <p tal:condition="view/error_message" 
       tal:content="structure view/error_message" class="error message"
      >Error message.</p>

    <p tal:condition="view/info_message" 
       tal:content="structure view/info_message" class="informational message"
      >Informational message.</p>

    <div tal:condition="view/invalid_fingerprint" class="error message">
      A malformed fingerprint was submitted. Did you enter your complete
      fingerprint correctly? A fingerprint is a long sequence of numbers
      and letters.  You should use the output produced by the command:
        <blockquote>
        <kbd>gpg --fingerprint</kbd>
        </blockquote>
      Please verify and try again.
    </div>

    <div tal:condition="view/key_already_imported" class="error message">
      The key <code tal:content="view/fingerprint" /> has already been imported.
    </div>

    <div tal:condition="view/key_retrieval_failed" class="error message">
      Launchpad could not import your OpenPGP key.
      <ul>
        <li>Did you enter your complete fingerprint correctly? A
        fingerprint is a long sequence of numbers and letters.
        You should use the output produced by the command:
        <blockquote>
        <kbd>gpg --fingerprint</kbd>
        </blockquote>
        </li>

        <li>Have you published your key to a public key
        server? You can do that by by entering in a terminal: 
        <blockquote>
        <kbd>gpg --keyserver keyserver.ubuntu.com --send-keys</kbd>
        </blockquote>
        </li>

        <li>Has your key been automatically mirrored to the Ubuntu key
        server? Keys sometimes take up to an hour to be synchronized
        between servers. You can check if it has <a tal:attributes="href
        view/keyserver_url">by querying the Ubuntu key server directly</a>.
        If it hasn't, you can publish directly to our server by entering in a
        terminal:
        <blockquote>
        <kbd>gpg --keyserver keyserver.ubuntu.com --send-keys</kbd>
        </blockquote>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <tal:has_key condition="view/key">
      <p tal:condition="view/key/revoked" class="error message">
        The key <span tal:replace="view/key/keyid" /> cannot be validated
        because it has been publicly revoked. You will need to generate a
        new key (using <kbd>gpg --genkey</kbd>) and repeat the process
        to import it.
      </p>

      <p tal:condition="view/key/expired" class="error message">
        The key <span tal:replace="view/key/keyid" /> cannot be validated
        because it has expired. Change the expiry date (in a terminal, enter
        <kbd>gpg --edit-key <var>your@e-mail.address</var></kbd> then enter
        <kbd>expire</kbd>), and try again.
      </p>

      <tal:key_ok condition="view/key_ok">
        <p tal:condition="view/key/can_encrypt" class="informational message">
          A message has been sent to <code
          tal:content="context/preferredemail/email">foo@bar.com</code>, encrypted
          with the key <code tal:content="view/key/displayname">DE233E22</code>.
          To confirm the key is yours, decrypt the message and follow the
          link inside.
        </p>
        <p tal:condition="not: view/key/can_encrypt" class="informational message">
          A message has been sent to <code
          tal:content="context/preferredemail/email">foo@bar.com</code>.
          To confirm the key <code
          tal:content="view/key/displayname">DA123F22</code> is yours,
          follow the link inside.
        </p>
      </tal:key_ok>
    </tal:has_key>

    <p>
      You can register your OpenPGP keys, which are
      created by software such as GnuPG.
      These are used to sign <a href="/codeofconduct">codes of conduct</a>,
      modify bugs through <a
      href="https://help.launchpad.net/BugTrackerEmailInterface">the email interface</a>,
      and to build and upload packages using <abbr>Soyuz</abbr>.
    </p>

    <form tal:condition="context/gpgkeys/count" 
          name="gpg_actions" action="" method="POST">
      <input type="hidden" name="action" value="deactivate_gpg" />

      <h2>Active keys</h2>

      <div tal:repeat="key context/gpgkeys">
        <label>
          <input type="checkbox" name="DEACTIVATE_GPGKEY"
                 tal:attributes="value key/id"/>
          <span tal:replace="key/displayname">KEY</span>
          <tal:block condition="not:key/can_encrypt">(sign only)</tal:block>
        </label>
      </div>
      <div><input type="submit" value="Deactivate Key" /></div>

      <p><dfn>Deactivating</dfn> a key <em>applies only to Launchpad</em>
      and not anywhere else. If you deactivate a key, it
      will automatically deactivate any feature that uses that key, such
      as a signed code of conduct, or the ability to comment on a bug
      report by e-mail.</p>

    </form>

    <form tal:condition="context/pendinggpgkeys" name="gpg_actions" 
          action="" method="POST">
      <input type="hidden" name="action" value="remove_gpgtoken" />

      <h2>Keys pending validation</h2>

      <div>
        <label tal:repeat="fingerprint context/pendinggpgkeys">
          <input type="checkbox" name="REMOVE_GPGTOKEN"
                 tal:attributes="value fingerprint"/>
          <span tal:replace="fingerprint">TOKEN</span>
        </label>
      </div>

      <input type="submit" value="Cancel Validation for Selected Keys" />
    </form>

    <form tal:condition="context/inactivegpgkeys" name="gpg_actions"
          action="" method="POST">
      <input type="hidden" name="action" value="reactivate_gpg" />

      <h2>Deactivated keys</h2>

      <p>If you changed your mind about deactivating a key, you can
      <dfn>reactivate</dfn> it.</p>

      <div tal:repeat="key context/inactivegpgkeys">
        <label>
        <input type="checkbox" name="REACTIVATE_GPGKEY"
               tal:attributes="value key/id"/>
          <span tal:replace="key/displayname">KEY</span>
          <tal:block condition="not:key/can_encrypt">(sign only)</tal:block>
        </label>
      </div>
      <input type="submit" value="Reactivate Key" />
    </form>

    <form name="gpg_actions" action="" method="POST">
      <input type="hidden" name="action" value="claim_gpg" />
      <h2>Importing an OpenPGP key</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          Ensure you already have a key. In a terminal window, enter:
          <pre>gpg --list-keys <var>your@e-mail.address</var></pre>
          If you have no key, create one:
          <pre>gpg --gen-key</pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          Ensure the key has been uploaded to a keyserver. To do this:
          <pre>gpg --send-key <var>key-id</var></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          Enter your key fingerprint. Use:
          <pre>gpg --fingerprint <var>key-id</var></pre>
          <table>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <th><label>Fingerprint:</label></th>
                <td><input type="text" size="50" name="fingerprint" /></td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="discreet">
                <th>Example:</th>
                <td>
                  <code>27E0 7815 B47C 0397 90D5&nbsp;&nbsp;8589 27D9 A27B F3F9 6058</code>
                </td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <p>
            Launchpad will e-mail
            <code tal:content="context/preferredemail/email"/> with instructions
            on finishing the process.
          </p>
          <div><input type="submit" name="import" value="Import Key"/></div>
        </li>
        </ol>
      </form>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
</tal:root>
